    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Front Cover, Vibration Damper, and Gerotor Oil Pump - Installation</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="7">
            <title>Front Cover</title>
            <figure id="f3000625" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj06/J06038.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Front cover crankcase dowels</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If removed, install front cover crankcase dowels.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Dowels may become lodged in front cover. Remove dowels and install in crankcase. If dowels are
                        bent, replace with new ones.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f3000626" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj06/J06039.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Locations for Liquid Gasket (RTV) application</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply Liquid Gasket (RTV) to joining surfaces of crankcase and lower crankcase. See
                    <hotlnk document="eges3001_140.xml" xrefid="e30006c">Special Service Tools</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, install and torque gasket and cover within five minutes of Liquid
                        Gasket (RTV) application to inhibit the formation of a skin and ensure a leak proof joint.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f3000627" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj06/J06040.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Front cover gasket installed</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position a new front cover gasket on the crankcase.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3000628" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj06/J06036.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installing the front cover</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align front cover with crankcase dowels.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3000629" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj06/J06034.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Front cover module retaining bolts</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 x 35 (17)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Fasten front cover assembly to crankcase with 17 bolts (M8 x 35) and tighten to the
                    <hotlnk document="eges3001_139.xml" xrefid="e30006b">Special Torque</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If removed, install water pump onto front cover with new O-ring. See
                    <hotlnk document="eges3001_135.xml" xrefid="a0607">"Water Pump Installation"</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3000630" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj06/J06041.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Heater feed tube O-ring</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate a new heater feed tube O-ring with the recommended coolant.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not lubricate heater feed tube O-ring with engine oil. Oil
                        produces a swelling effect on O-ring, resulting in leakage.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f3000631" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj06/J06042.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Torquing the heater feed tube assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Nut, M10</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M6 x 14</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install heater feed tube into front cover while aligning bracket slot with stud at
                    lifting eye. Install bolt (M6 x 14) into front cover and tighten to the
                    <hotlnk document="eges3001_311.xml" xrefid="S300GTG">Standard Torque</hotlnk>. Tighten nut to the
                    <hotlnk document="eges3001_139.xml" xrefid="e30006b">Special Torque</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
